  <body id="groupserver-manual"
    tal:define="siteName python:options['siteName'];">
    <section>
      <h>Help</h>

      <p>You can get help with using 
        <span class="site" 
          tal:content="siteName">this site</span> 
        from
        <cite href="manual">The 
          <span class="site" tal:content="siteName">OnlineGroups.Net</span> 
          User Manual,</cite>
        or from the context-sensitive help-links:
        <a href="/help/manual/#groupserver-getting-help-from-context"
          class="helpLink">[?]</a>.
        In addition, assistance on participating in online groups is
        available from 
        <cite href="participation">The
          <span class="site" tal:content="siteName">OnlineGroups.Net</span>
          User Guide.</cite>
      </p>
      
      <tal:block
        tal:define="divisionObject python:here.Scripts.get.division_object();
        divisionName python:divisionObject and (divisionObject.getId() != 'ogs' and '%s_' % divisionObject.getId()) or '';
        supportEmail python:'%ssupport@onlinegroups.net' % divisionName"
        tal:condition="python:'Authenticated' in user.getRolesInContext(divisionObject)">
        <p>
          If you have a question that is not answered in this Help section, 
          please raise it in 
          <a title="Groups Homepage" href="/groups">your online groups,</a>
          or directly with the Participation Coach in the relevant
          group
          <a href="/help/manual/#groupserver-getting-help-from-the-participation-coach"
            class="helpLink">[?]</a>.
          If your question is still unanswered, you 
          can address it to
          <a class="emaillink" title="Email to the support group"
            tal:attributes="href string:mailto:${supportEmail}" 
            tal:content="supportEmail"/>, or from 
          OnlineGroups.Net
          <a href="/help/manual/#groupserver-getting-help-from-onlinegroups-support"
          class="helpLink">[?]</a>.
        </p>
      </tal:block>
    </section>
  </body>
</html>